// stressed long vowels:
// a series of changes occur:
// first, vowel breaking
eː > ej / ˈ_
ɛː > ea / ˈ_
oː > ow / ˈ_
ɔː > oa / ˈ_
// then, some shifts:
ej > iː
ˈea > eə
ow > aw
ˈoa > wˈa
// and more breaking
iː > aj / ˈ_
uː > aw / ˈ_
// at this point, the only remaining long monophthong is /ˈaː/ < *ahə
// note that /eː/ and /iː/ merge to /aj/, and /oː/ and /uː/ merge to /aw/
